# Design Bible (mandatory for UI work)

Before writing or changing **any** UI, styling, layout, colours, typography, or components:

1. Read **`docs/design-bible/00-design-tokens.md`** first
2. Read **`docs/design-bible/brand/SuggaPlay_Master_Design_Bible_1.pdf`** and **`SuggaPlay_Editorial_Design_Bible_2.pdf`**
3. Review **`docs/design-bible/screens/`** reference images
4. Cross-reference `docs/22-ui-design-system.md` for Tailwind/shadcn mapping only

## Rules

- **Do not guess** colours, fonts, border radius, spacing, or layout if the design bible specifies them
- **Do not** copy Secret Benefits or generic dating-site aesthetics unless the design bible says so
- **Match mockups** in `docs/design-bible/screens/` pixel-close where specs exist
- If the design bible is **silent** on a detail, ask the user — do not invent premium brand styling
- Export design tokens (CSS variables / Tailwind theme) from the bible into `app/globals.css` when building the design system step

## Priority order

1. `docs/design-bible/` — visual truth
2. `docs/00-product-bible.md` — brand tone & positioning
3. `docs/22-ui-design-system.md` — implementation conventions
4. Existing shadcn/ui defaults — **lowest** priority; override to match bible
